  <front>
   <head>SONG.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">voice is this, thou evening gale!</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That mingles with thy rising wail;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And, as it passes, sadly seems</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The faint return of youthful dreams?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Though now its strain is wild and drear,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Blythe was it once as sky-lark's cheer —</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Sweet as the night-bird's sweetest song —</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Dear as the lisp of Infant's tongue.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">It was the voice, at whose sweet flow</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The heart did beat, and cheek did glow,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And lip did smile, and eye did weep,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And motioned love the measure keep.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Oft be thy sound, soft gale of even,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thus to my wistful fancy given;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And, as I list the swelling strain,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The dead shall seem to live again.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
